The course aims at an extensive development of vocabulary for use in different situations. The main emphasis is on developing medical terminology both in the oral and written form. The course introduces medical vocabulary related to the following topics:
1. Bodyparts. Meeting the patient (personal data). 
2. Therapeutic exercises. 
3. Anamnesis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim of the course is to expand student&acute;s specialized vocabulary and oral skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course the student can: 
* understand short and simple texts related to their future professions;
* use specialized medical terminology learned during the course and apply the acquired vocabulary to their working lives;
* take part in conversations, present and explain his point of view regarding the course themes;
* correctly use the terminology and grammar acquired during the course;
* use the acquired terminology both in oral and written form.
